 example and behaviour driven development.\r\nGojko is a frequent speaker at leading software development and testing conferences and runs the UK Agile Testing User Group.  \r\nOver the last eleven years, he has worked as a developer, architect, technical director and consultant on projects delivering financial and energy trading platforms, mobile positioning and e-commerce applications, online gaming and complex configuration management systems.\r\nHe is the author of 2 best-selling books: Specification by Example & Bridging the Communication Gap, as well as Test Driven .NET Development with FitNesse and The Secret Ninja Cucumber Scrolls. </p></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>课程主要模块：</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"summary\">\r\n	<li>Exposing Problems with Imperative Requirements；</li>\r\n	<li>Communicating with Examples；</li>\r\n	<li>What Makes a Good Specification with Examples/Acceptance Tests；</li>\r\n	<li>Key Process Patterns；</li>\r\n<div class=\"clear\"></div> \r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>课程概要：</h3>\r\n“From User Stories to Acceptance Tests – Specification by Example/BDD Fundamentals” （从用户故事到接受测试－实例化需求分析／行为驱动开发基础工作坊）is an interactive training workshop, aimed at providing skills to bridge the communication gap between stakeholders and implementation teams, build quality into software from the start, design, develop and deliver systems fit for purpose by applying emerging collaborative requirements management, specification and testing practices in agile and lean processes.\r\n\r\nThe workshop is based on Gojko Adzic\'s books Bridging the Communication Gap and Specification by Example, as well as years of practical experience with many teams in different contexts. It is very interactive and practical, focused on providing participants with first-hand real world experience and aimed at cross-functional training groups of business analysts, product owners, developers and testers.\r\n\r\n<h3>报名咨询：</h3>\r\n<p class=\"tel\">Tel: 021-63809913</p>\r\n<p class=\"emai